  "title": "Dental Assistant / Senior Dental Assistant #81684",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Medical and dental practice activities</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Dental Assistant / Senior Dental Assistant</strong></li><li>Working Location: Orchard Road</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 Days, Monday to Friday 9:30am - 6:30pm, Saturday 9:30am - 2:30pm & Sunday 9:30am – 1pm (Follow roster)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic $1600 - $3500 + AWS + Performance Bonus + Dental Benefits + Healthcare Insurance</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Share patient care information and instructions given by the Dentist (e.g., post-treatment instructions, oral hygiene guidance)</li><li>Assist the Dentist during procedures by passing the correct instruments and supporting patient care</li><li>Prepare and set up the treatment area before the patient arrives, ensuring instrument trays, materials, and equipment are ready</li><li>Assist with taking and processing dental diagnostic X-rays</li><li>Support lab-related tasks such as case tracking, casting, impressions, and retainer fabrication</li><li>Check, pack, and sterilize instruments and instrument sets</li><li>Clean and maintain dental chairs, equipment, work surfaces, and instruments according to infection control standards</li><li>Ensure clinic rooms have enough sterile instruments and instrument sets for daily use</li><li>Assist in receiving and managing patient feedback</li><li>Report any incidents such as equipment malfunction, defects, or missing instruments promptly</li><li>Support stocktaking and inform the in-charge when inventory is running low; store instruments and supplies properly using the first-in, first-out (FIFO) method</li><li>Other ad hoc tasks assigned by Manager / PIC</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Min. N level / O level</li><li>Min. 1 year experience as dental assistant</li><li>Knowledge of dental instruments and sterilization methods</li><li>Understanding of health & safety regulations</li><li>Good computer skills</li><li>Proficiency in Chinese is advantageous to communicate with Chinese speaking clients.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Kindly apply through ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81684 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
